The South African Weather Service (Saws) has warned of severe
thunderstorms expected over western and central parts of northern KwaZulu-Natal
with the possibility of severe lightning, heavy downpours and damaging winds. Isolated to scattered showers and thundershowers are
expected over most parts of KwaZulu-Natal, with some expected to become severe
over the northern parts of the province on Sunday afternoon, said the weather service. Saws said the areas which are likely to be affected are
Abaqulusi, Alfred Duma – Idaka, Alfred Duma – Ladysmith, Dannhauser, eDumbe,
eMadlangeni, Endumeni, Inkosi Langalibalele _ Estcourt, Inkosi Langalibalele _
Sobabili, Mpofana – Mooi River, Msinga, Newcastle, Nkandla, Nquthu, Okhahlamba,
Ulundi, Umvoti and uPongolo.